# Vercel Speed Insights Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the Next.js (App Router) project following the latest official Vercel documentation.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- **Added dependency**: `@vercel/speed-insights` version `^2.0.0`
- **Package manager**: pnpm
- **File modified**: `apps/web/package.json`
- **Lockfile updated**: `apps/web/pnpm-lock.yaml`

### 2. Component Integration
- **File modified**: `apps/web/src/app/layout.tsx`
- **Import added**: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";`
- **Component placement**: Added `<SpeedInsights />` component in the root layout's `<body>` tag, right after the closing `</ThemeProvider>` tag

### 3. Implementation Details
The Speed Insights component was added to the root layout file (`src/app/layout.tsx`) following Next.js App Router best practices:
- Used the framework-specific import from `@vercel/speed-insights/next`
- Placed the component at the root level to track all pages in the application
- Preserved all existing code structure and formatting
- No breaking changes to existing functionality

## Verification Steps Completed
✅ TypeScript type checking passed (`pnpm run typecheck`)
✅ ESLint linting passed with no errors (`pnpm run lint`)
✅ Code compilation successful
✅ Lockfile properly updated with new dependency

## Next Steps (Manual)
To complete the Speed Insights setup:
1. Enable Speed Insights in your Vercel dashboard:
   - Navigate to your project in Vercel
   - Select "Speed Insights" from the sidebar
   - Click "Enable" button
2. Deploy the application to Vercel
3. Visit your deployed site to generate traffic
4. View Speed Insights data in your Vercel dashboard

## Technical Notes
- The implementation follows the official Vercel Speed Insights quickstart guide fetched on 2026-06-14
- Speed Insights will automatically track Core Web Vitals (LCP, FID, CLS, etc.)
- No additional configuration is required - the component works out of the box
- The component is lightweight and has minimal performance impact
